            "answer_text": "The scientific designator in which the first name (genus) and the secondary name (specific epithet) are the same is known as tautonym. The reason (from the same page) is that such a name \u201cimplicitly indicates that the species is the type of its genus\u201d. This type of naming convention (nomenclature) is applicable only in description based on animal diversity (i. e. zoology). ",
